-- Oil Advances For Second Day Amid Iran Tensions, U.S. Economic Data Reports
-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   S c h m o l l i n g e r
-- 2011-12-29T23:08:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/oil-advances-for-second-day-amid-iran-tensions-u-s-economic-data-reports.html
Oil rose for a second day in New
York amid potential supply disruptions by  Iran  around the Strait
of Hormuz and on signs that the economy of the U.S. is
improving, spurring fuel demand.  Crude oil for February delivery gained as much as 19 cents,
0.2 percent, to $99.84 a barrel on the  New York Mercantile
Exchange . Prices are set for a 9.2 percent rise this year after
climbing 15 percent in 2010.  Brent oil for February settlement yesterday rose 45 cents,
or 0.4 percent, to $108.01 a barrel on the London-based ICE
Futures Europe Exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christian Schmollinger in Singapore at 
